    "lesson_plan_custom_additions": "Customize phiaj xwm kawm generation nrog specific requirements. Examples: Kuvnclude a bell-ringer kev ua, Ntxiv SEL tshawb-in moment, Siv 5E model structure, Kuvnclude station rotation, Ntxiv techtsis yoglogy integration section, thiab Kuvnclude niam txiv communication tsis yogte. AKuv incorporates koj ntxivitions into tsimd lus qhia structure. Requirements can specify: ntxivitional sections (warmup, closure), specific strategies (think-pair-share, jigsaw), sij hawm allocations (15-min direct instruction max), thiab format elements (table rau differentiation, tshawblist rau materials). Mullus pable ntxivitions can be combined. Tshem instructions produce better qhov tshwm sims. Lus Pab: Kuvnclude koj must-have elements that AKuv might tsis yogt include by default.",
    "adventure_input_mode": "Xaiv primary interaction style rau koj kev mus txawv teb chaws. Mullus pable Choice: Tub Ntxhais Kawms xaiv los ntawm 4 AKuv-tsimd kev xaivs each turn—easiest mode, zoo heev rau kojnger learners thiab structured lus qhias. Debate Mode: Tub Ntxhais Kawms must persuade NPCs through reasoned arguments—builds rhetoric thiab critical thinking. System Simulation: Tub Ntxhais Kawms manage khoom sivs (gqub, reputation, supplies) while making decisions—incorporates math thiab casiv-effect reasoning. Each mode changes gamentaus feel significantly. Choice mode focsivs on narrative; Debate builds argumentation; System teaches khoom siv management. Mix modes across different kev mus txawv teb chawss rau varied skill development.",
